    "narrative": "Our strongest play today is **Tyler Freeman** (71.80), who benefits from a prime matchup against Walker Buehler. His score is bolstered by a significant 14% park factor boost and the fact that Buehler\u2019s slow delivery profiles well for our heavy emphasis on stolen base potential. Joining him in the top tier are **Will Smith** (69.22) and **Gleyber Torres** (67.52). **Gleyber Torres** is a particularly high-upside play, as he leverages a 13% dynamic platoon advantage against a weak matchup in DL Hall, while **Will Smith** remains a consistent anchor assuming he retains the #3 spot in the lineup.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench today was **Bryson Stott** (45.81). While he remains an elite asset for our stolen base-starved roster, the combination of a negative platoon split against Matthew Boyd and a drop in his projected order spot pushed him just outside our starting criteria. Similarly, we are exercising caution with **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (54.07); despite his superstar status, he faces a tough assignment against Peter Lambert, and the optimizer suggests that his current efficiency does not outweigh the higher-scoring profiles of players like **Wenceel Perez** (66.93) or **Daulton Varsho** (61.65). \n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding our lineup assumptions, as **Will Smith**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Matt Chapman**, and **Gavin Sheets** are currently listed as \"Lineup Pending.\" While we have projected them in high-leverage spots, any shift to the bottom of the order will trigger an immediate re-evaluation of their daily efficiency scores. Furthermore, the presence of Shohei Ohtani on the mound serves as a major red flag for **Matt Chapman** and keeps **Luis Arraez** and **Jung Hoo Lee** firmly on the bench, as their scoring ceilings are severely capped by the elite opposing arm.",
